cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about generating natural language sentences with controlled attributes using a neural generative model. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses variational auto-encoders and discriminators, which are common techniques in machine learning and deep learning, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves learning disentangled latent representations, which is a topic of interest in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions collaborative learning, which is a technique used in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of text generation compared to visual domain, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) may also be a relevant sub-category.
